<span id="freeTextContainer929812389763906695">This is a achingly beautiful book. It is hard to describe because not much external &quot;action&quot; occurs but the movement of the heart is remarkable. The story of Father Hugh Kennedy, a recovering alcoholic, and his reconnecting with the Carmodys is wonderfully told. O&apos;Connor has a gift of understanding prayer, loneliness, despair, hope, faith. I am not doing this book justice. It is so beautiful. It will stick with me for a long time.</span>
  <span id="freeText929812389763906695" style="display:none">This is a achingly beautiful book. It is hard to describe because not much external "action" occurs but the movement of the heart is remarkable. The story of Father Hugh Kennedy, a recovering alcoholic, and his reconnecting with the Carmodys is wonderfully told. O'Connor has a gift of understanding prayer, loneliness, despair, hope, faith. I am not doing this book justice. It is so beautiful. It will stick with me for a long time.</span>
